35. Write a PHP script using an array that checks if a string contains another string and displays the result.
CODE:
<?php
$strings = array("Hello World", "PHP is fun", "Learn programming");

// String to search for
$search = "PHP";

// Loop through array and check if each string contains the search word
foreach ($strings as $str) {
    if (strpos($str, $search) !== false) {
        echo "'$search' found in: $str\n";
    } else {
        echo "'$search' not found in: $str\n";
    }
}
?>

OUTPUT:
'PHP' not found in: Hello World 'PHP' found in: PHP is fun 'PHP' not found in: Learn programming
